The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, December 26, 2003 				 Xmas vacation
																								New Delhi, Dec. 25 (PTI): The Centre has agreed to restore the original Christmas vacation in Kendriya Vidyalayas in Kerala this year.																								Human resource development minister Murli Manohar Joshi agreed to stick to the earlier routine after minister of state for law and justice P.C. Thomas conveyed the sentiments of the people of the state, sources said.																								The decision to shift the winter holidays in these schools to January also came in for sharp criticism in Parliament last week with the Opposition alleging that it hurt the sentiments of the christians.
